<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">J. Malcolm Garcia</span></strong> lives in Winnetka, Illinois, and is the author of <em>The Khaarijee: A Chronicle of Friendship and War in Kabul</em> and <em>Riding through Katrina with the Red Baron&rsquo;s Ghost</em>. He is inspired by the journalist Martha Gellhorn, who reported from Panama at the age of eighty-one, and he hopes he too will be writing and traveling in his eighties.</p><a href="/contributors/j-malcolm-garcia" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

